Subject: [PATCH] ia64/mm: remove orphan #endif in init.c

The v5.5 patch had two hunks for init.c: hunk #1 added
#ifdef CONFIG_ARCH_HAS_SYNC_DMA_FOR_CPU before arch_sync_dma_for_cpu(),
hunk #2 added #endif after it.  When applied to v5.10, hunk #1 was
rejected (function renamed to arch_dma_mark_clean()), but hunk #2
applied — leaving an orphan #endif that causes a build error.

The #ifdef guard is no longer needed in v5.10 since
ARCH_HAS_DMA_MARK_CLEAN is unconditionally selected and the function
is always compiled.  Remove the stray #endif.

---
 arch/ia64/mm/init.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/ia64/mm/init.c
+++ b/arch/ia64/mm/init.c
@@ -81,7 +81,6 @@
 		set_bit(PG_arch_1, &pfn_to_page(pfn)->flags);
 	} while (++pfn <= PHYS_PFN(paddr + size - 1));
 }
-#endif
 
 inline void
 ia64_set_rbs_bot (void)
